President Muhammadu Buhari and other West African leaders are currently meeting over the crisis in Mali. The extraordinary summit of the ECOWAS leaders is holding virtually. This was confirmed by Buhari’s Special Assistant on New Media, Bashir Ahmaad. Ahmaad tweeted: “President @MBuhari and other ECOWAS leaders are meeting (virtually) today to discuss the military coup in Mali that ousted President Ibrahim Boubacar Keita.” DAILY POST recalls that President Ibrahim Keita and his government resigned after soldiers arrested him. The soldiers have set up a body to work out modalities for elections in the country.